<$fill $name="body">

!! Components

* ''`functions.tid`'' -- shared filter functions for path resolution, child discovery, context filtering. Used by both the tool and the browser UI.
* ''`tool.tid`'' -- the `llm_help` MCP tool, tagged `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tool`. Renders wikitext pages and lists children.
* ''`settings.tid`'' -- help browser UI with breadcrumb navigation, content area, child cards, and user shortcut management.
* ''`styles.tid`'' -- CSS for the browser UI components.

!! Help page tiddler convention

Every help page is a tiddler tagged `$:/tags/rimir/llm-help/page` with fields:

|!Field |!Required |!Description |
|`llm-help-path` |yes |Space-separated paths (e.g., `data-model/person/create actions/create/person`) |
|`llm-help-description` |yes |One-line description shown in parent listings |
|`llm-help-sort` |no |Numeric sort within siblings (default: alphabetical) |
|`llm-help-context` |no |Space-separated context keys for visibility filtering |

!! Path resolution

Paths are stored in the `llm-help-path` field, not derived from tiddler titles. This allows any plugin to mount content at any path while keeping tiddlers under its own namespace.

Multi-path: A page with `llm-help-path: data-model/person/create actions/create/person` appears at both paths.

!! Child discovery

For a given path, the system:

# Collects all visible pages' paths via `_llm-help-all-paths`
# Filters to paths starting with `<requested-path>/`
# Extracts the next path segment after the prefix
# Deduplicates and sorts

Virtual parent nodes are synthesized automatically when children exist but no explicit page does.

!! Context filtering

Context uses set-intersection: a page is visible if it has no `llm-help-context` (always visible) or if any of its context keys match any of the active context keys.

Active context comes from `$:/temp/rimir/llm-help/active-context` (set by the environment, e.g., appify sets it when an app becomes active) or the tool's optional `context` parameter. Uses `$:/temp/` so it resets on reload — correct because context reflects what's active right now, not a permanent preference.

!! Dynamic content

All pages are wikitext, rendered at tool-call time via the llm-connect tool executor. Pages can use `$importvariables`, `$list`, `$let`, filters, etc. to read schemas, enumerate instances, or compute anything from the wiki store.

Example: The orga plugin's type pages import `typed/functions.tid` and render the live schema for each type, including field definitions, constraints, and existing instances.

